title: Japan election 2026 explained: Who won, who lost and who is Sanae Takaichi?
summary_full: Japan's ruling LDP, led by Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi, is projected to win Sunday's snap election by a landslide, securing a commanding majority. This victory is expected to empower Takaichi to advance her conservative agenda, including potential revisions to Japan's pacifist constitution. The result marks a significant revival for the LDP, overcoming recent challenges.
